----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                             OpenC2X
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
When OpenC2X source is organised in the tree structure like this:
.
├── build
└── src
    ├── CMakeLists.txt
    ├── cam
    ├── common
    ├── dcc
    ├── denm
    ├── denmApp
    ├── gps
    ├── httpServer
    ├── ldm
    ├── obd2
    └── kernel-patches

Follow the steps mentioned below in sequence to get OpenC2X up and running.



----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                      Set up the environment
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open a terminal and run the following command

    $ sudo apt-get install libzmq3-dev libboost-all-dev protobuf-compiler libprotobuf-dev \
libgps-dev gpsd gpsd-clients libnl-3-200 libnl-3-dev libnl-genl-3-200 libnl-genl-3-dev sqlite3 \
libsqlite3-dev tmux asn1c build-essential cmake doxygen



----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                           Generate source from asn before compiling
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open a terminal, navigate to asn1 folder in common:

    $ cd /path_to_my_project/src/common/asn1/
    $ ./generate.sh



----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                         Compiling
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Open a terminal, navigate to your project root folder and configure the project:

    $ cd /path_to_my_project/build
    $ cmake ../src
    $ make all

- The executables can be found in corresponding module folders found in build/binaries/<module>/bin/
- The config of the modules can be changed in build/binaries/<module>/config/
- To run OpenC2X, you can also use the script startOpenC2X.sh in scripts directory.

For setting up kernel, go through kernel-patches/README.txt


